{"paperId": "df17247de8bf11c0c461bbfe11a4750c03d58ea5", "abstract": "We present a new approach for fast and controllable generation of symbolic music based on the simplex diffusion, which is essentially a diffusion process operating on probabilities rather than the signal space. This objective has been applied in domains such as natural language processing but here we apply it to generating 4-bar multi-instrument music loops using an orderless representation. We show that our model can be steered with vocabulary priors, which affords a considerable level control over the music generation process, for instance, infilling in time and pitch and choice of instrumentation -- all without task-specific model adaptation or applying extrinsic control.", "venue": "arXiv.org", "year": 2024, "citationCount": 0, "influentialCitationCount": 0, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "It is shown that the model can be steered with vocabulary priors, which affords a considerable level control over the music generation process, for instance, infilling in time and pitch and choice of instrumentation -- all without task-specific model adaptation or applying extrinsic control."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [0.6291518211364746, 1.1724307537078857, -0.35128599405288696, 0.2553477883338928, -0.2190903276205063, -0.4649370014667511, 0.5755760073661804, -0.22287724912166595, 0.05389847233891487, -0.41396012902259827, 0.5173196792602539, 0.16246820986270905, -0.49505361914634705, 0.056695520877838135, -0.22655634582042694, -0.2129763811826706, -1.1003069877624512, 0.6006476879119873, 0.2825169563293457, -0.43764644861221313, 0.08339185267686844, -0.6065248847007751, -0.9045382142066956, -0.1548680067062378, 0.03748610243201256, 0.5387096405029297, -0.29420268535614014, 1.1862859725952148, -0.11764846742153168, 0.15683306753635406, 0.33035752177238464, -0.1456201672554016, 0.563444972038269, -0.42994529008865356, 0.3281744718551636, -0.2789419889450